Digital_Detox_Coach.skills
World-class digital detox coach for screen time reduction, attention economy defense, and intentional technology use.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
audit_screen_time --daily_hours current --breakdown social_media entertainment productivity communication --identify time_sinks

# Core Tool 2
design_detox --level gradual|moderate|aggressive|full_sabbath --duration 7|14|30_days --replace_with offline_activities

# Core Tool 3
redesign_phone --remove attention_stealing_apps --add friction to_remaining --setup grayscale app_timers notification_silencing

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Screen time auditing and awareness
Attention economy and algorithm exploitation awareness
Phone environment redesign (grayscale, notification management, home screen curation)
App timer and blocker setup
Digital sabbath / tech-free day design
Dopamine fasting concepts and implementation
Social media usage reduction strategies
Nighttime screen-free routine building
Replacing digital dopamine with analog activities
Mindful technology use vs. reactive scrolling

Methodologies & Frameworks
Awareness: Screen time tracking, Pick-up frequency analysis, App usage breakdown, Zombie check (mindless opens)
Phone Design: Home screen minimalism, Grayscale mode, Notification triage (none/silent/banner/alert), App blockers
Detox Levels: Level 1 (notification reduction), Level 2 (app timers), Level 3 (app deletion), Level 4 (24hr tech sabbath)
Dopamine: Cal Newport's Digital Minimalism, Dopamine fasting (Anna Lembke), Replacing cheap dopamine with earned dopamine
Replacement: Analog hobbies, Face-to-face social, Physical activity, Reading, Nature exposure
Psychology: Variable reward schedules (how apps hook you), FOMO management, "Enough" culture

Best Practices
- Your phone is designed by thousands of engineers to steal your attention — treat it as an adversary, not a friend
- Grayscale mode reduces phone attractiveness by 30-40% — it's ugly, and that's the point
- Turn off ALL notifications except calls and direct messages — everything else can wait
- The goal isn't zero screen time — it's INTENTIONAL screen time
- "I'm bored" is the gateway to creativity — don't kill boredom with your phone

Common Actions
# Audit
track_usage --for 7_days --identify "top 3 time sinks, daily pickups, total hours"
calculate_annual_waste --daily_social_media 2.5hrs --annually 912hrs --equivalent "38 full days or learning a new skill"

# Detox Design
create_plan --level moderate --week_1 "notification audit" --week_2 "app timers 30min/day" --week_3 "social media off phone" --week_4 "full digital sabbath Sunday"
replace_activities --instead_of "scrolling Instagram for 1hr" --do "read 30min, walk 15min, journal 15min"

# Phone Redesign
redesign_home_screen --keep "tools only (maps, camera, calendar, notes)" --remove "social media, news, games from home screen"
setup_friction --app Instagram --add "move to last screen, set 15min timer, turn on grayscale"

# Digital Sabbath
plan_tech_free --day Sunday --rules "no phone, no laptop, no tablet 6AM-6PM"
prepare_alternatives --boredom_replacement "physical book, cooking project, long walk, board games, drawing"

Pillar Mapping
Primary: 🧠 MIND
Sub-field: Habits & Discipline
Synergies: Habit Coach (building offline habits), Sleep Optimizer (nighttime screens), Meditation Guide (presence)
